 A 25-year old Fulani kidnap-for-ransom kingpin, Ibrahim Umar, stunned people watching as he was being paraded among 15 others by the Nigerian Police, Tuesday, when he disclosed that he had not only killed over ten of his kidnapped victims in recent times but also drank their blood raw. January 2, 2018 In "Crime Alert" The Lagos State Police Command has arrested a 10-man suspected kidnap gang said to be responsible for series of abductions in Ajah and Ibeju-Lekki areas of Lagos. July 16, 2013 In "News" A 38-year-old driver with a hotel in Victoria Island area of Lagos, Williams Olowoloju, yesterday, disclosed that he masterminded the kidnap of his boss’ brother-in-law and his lover, with the intention of raising money for his father-in-law’s burial billed for November 19. November 1, 2017 In "News"